summary:
18. Supports enhancing the Secretary-General's role in conflict prevention, including increased use of fact-finding and confidence-building missions.
19. Endorses the Secretary-General's call for support to regional prevention strategies and increased resources for regional capacities.
The Security Council:

 Calls for enhancing conflict prevention capacity of regional organizations, particularly in Africa, by providing international assistance to the Organization of African Unity, its successor, the Economic Community of West African States, and their respective conflict prevention mechanisms;
 Stresses addressing root causes of armed conflict to create conditions for durable peace and sustainable development, and calls for implementing the UN Declaration and Programme of Action for a Culture of Peace;
 Looks forward to further consideration of the Secretary-General's report on Prevention of Armed Conflict by the General Assembly, Economic and Social Council, and other actors;
 Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
